import React from 'react' const UserIncome = ({ user }) => { var income = user.income income = income.substring(1) var car = user.car return (
{ (car === "BMW" || car === "Mercedes-Benz") && (income < 5) ? <> {user.id} {user.first_name} {user.last_name} {user.email} {user.gender} {user.income} {user.city} {user.car} {user.quote} : <> }
) } export default UserIncome
